headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo's absence couldn't prevent the Milwaukee Bucks from extending the longest winning streak in the NBA this season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks outlast Suns 104-101 for 14th consecutive victory

headlines.description: — Waiting for just the right moment to launch his game-winning shot was no problem for Trae Young. He says he has been envisioning similar shots since he was a kid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young's buzzer-beating jumper lifts Hawks past Nets 129-127

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan scored 29 points, Zach LaVine added 27 and the Chicago Bulls overcame their shooting woes from long range Sunday to beat the Washington Wizards 102-82.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan, LaVine combine for 56, Bulls zoom past Wizards

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Anthony Davis dunked a missed shot and screamed after giving the Los Angeles Lakers the lead for good with two minutes to go.
headlines.shortLinkText: Davis leads rally from 27 down as Lakers beat Mavs 111-108

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 35 points and Jarrett Allen had 23 points and 11 rebounds, sending the Cleveland Cavaliers to a 118-93 victory over the Toronto Raptors on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell scores 35 points, Cavaliers rout Raptors 118-93

events.name: Sacramento Kings at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Sacramento Kings coach Mike Brown was worried his team might come out flat two days after one of the wildest games in NBA history.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fox scores 33 as Kings beat Thunder for 3rd straight win

events.name: Minnesota Timberwolves at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — So close to a playoff spot in the clogged-up Western Conference standings, this win meant so much for coach Steve Kerr’s undermanned Golden State Warriors — for many reasons.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thompson, Warriors' supporting cast hold off Timberwolves

events.name: Houston Rockets at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — The celebration surrounding Damian Lillard’s record-breaking performance was short-lived.
headlines.shortLinkText: Blazers' Lillard has 71 pts and 13 3s, then gets drug tested

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 40 points, 17 rebounds and 10 assists to lead the Denver Nuggets to a 134-124 overtime victory against the Los Angeles Clippers in a matchup of Western Conference contenders Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: George's heave just late, Jokic and Nuggets top Clips in OT
